  "text": "(2) Upon expansion of the plume, temperature and pressure decrease. Heat is also conveyed to water and, if the cooling rate is sufficiently high, the liquid carbon becomes super cooled, and at this point nucleation of NDs is initiated. Liquid droplets formation, as quantitatively described in the paper of Mazzi et al. [CITATION_1] helps to explain the formation of NDs. (3) Growth of diamond nuclei continues as long as pressure and temperature favor the crystallization of liquid into diamond nuclei.",
